	<text>
		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002099_0001"/><!--pb/@n='15r'-->
<lb/><p rend="center"><space extent="1" unit="words"/>30 Oct<hi rend="sup">r</hi></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>1864</p><!--printed letterhead--><!--
<p rend="right">NEWSTEAD ABBEY</p>
<p rend="right">MANSFIELD</p>
<p rend="right">NOTTS</p>
--><!--printed letterhead ends here-->
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>A series of papers 
<lb/>has been begun 
<lb/>yesterday in the 
<lb/>"Field" by a <persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Waghorn</persName>
<lb/>who was attached 
<lb/>to <persName>Bishop<del type="strikethrough">'s</del> Tozer<reg>'</reg>s</persName>
<lb/>mission with 
<lb/>the intimation 
<lb/>that he was 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002099_0002"/><!--pb/@n='15v'-->
<lb/>"in connection with 
<lb/>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Livingstone<reg>'</reg>s 
<lb/>Expedition" - Would 
<lb/>it be well to say 
<lb/>to the Editor that 
<lb/>he was <hi rend="underline">not</hi> of 
<lb/>my party? or 
<lb/>would it be a 
<lb/>good advertisement? 
<lb/>or would it be 
<lb/>considered by the 
<lb/>public cantankerous 
<lb/>on my part? 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002099_0003"/><!--pb/@n='16r'-->
<lb/>My good friends 
<lb/>here think that I 
<lb/>had better contradict 
<lb/>him in justice to 
<lb/>you &amp; myself as 
<lb/>people may say 
<lb/>that they have 
<lb/>already read all 
<lb/>about the Expedition 
<lb/>in the "Field" &amp; 
<lb/>not buy the book<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>This which I have 
<lb/>glanced over is 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002099_0004"/><!--pb/@n='16v'-->
<lb/><choice><sic>is</sic><corr>notext</corr></choice> chiefly about 
<lb/>hunting. <choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>he man 
<lb/>is a sort of fool<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>If you can convenient
<lb/>ly answer this before 
<lb/>the next publication 
<lb/>of the "Field" I shall 
<lb/>be obliged.</p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Yours ever</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">All from the <persName>bishop</persName>
<lb/>down to <persName>Waghorn</persName> liked 
<lb/>very much to call 
<w>them-<lb break="no"/>selves</w> of D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> L's Expedition 
<lb/>which perhaps was 
<lb/>complimentary though they didn<reg>'</reg>t 
<lb/>mean it<reg>.</reg></p>
			
